         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">30/4/96. ¶  ¶ According to the wish, expressed in your last letter, dear Dr Dyer, I have obtained from Mess Blogg some samples of their Australian-Acacia-Scent, and they present it to the Kew Museum i...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">96.04.30</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1891-6, f. 83.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Date stamped</seg>: Royal Gardens Kew 8 JUN 96: <seg style="font-style: italic; ">annotated in black ink by</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">[?J. Hillier</seg>]: Thanks herewith to Messrs Blogg per Sir F. von Mueller 70/1896 18.6.96 JM[H], <seg style="font-style: italic; ">and in black ink by</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">[?W. Hemsley</seg>]: Ansd 27.6.96 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">(letter not found)</seg>.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See annotation (note 3) <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on M to W. Thisleton Dyer, 11 January 1896.</p>
               </note>30/4/96.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>According to the wish, expressed in your last letter, dear Dr Dyer, I have obtained from Mess Blogg some samples of their Australian-Acacia-Scent, and they present it to the Kew Museum in an elegant form.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">Once received at Kew, the samples were referred to the London perfumers Piesse &amp; Lubin, who reported back on 23 June 1896; see </seg>C. Pleisse to J. Jackson, 23 June 1896 (in this edition as M96-06-23). A copy of Piesse's report was sent to M on 27 June but has not been found.</p>
               </note> They have obtained Lord Brassey's<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Governor of Vic., 1895-9.</p>
               </note> patronage for their perfumes on my own initiatory steps, as these Gentlemen have invented processes of their own for their large factory and elaborate machinery.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hitherto this firm has only produced the perfume of <name key="Acacia%20mollissima">Acacia mollissima</name> which is therefore that, which you have to catalogue.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The sample remains in the Economic Botany collection at Kew, under <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Acacia decurrens</seg> var <seg style="font-style: italic; ">mollis</seg>, catalogue number 58564, entry book number 70.1896.</p>
               </note> I suggested also to them to try the powerfully scented and copiously flowering A. pycnantha.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As through me the Balcan<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Balkan?</p>
               </note> Oil Rose, Rosa (Gallica) Damascena var trigintipetala became introduced into Australia, Mess Blogg will also commence to distill the “Attar” here.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Always regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Acacia%20mollissima">Acacia mollissima</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Acacia%20pycnantha">Acacia pycnantha</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">Rosa damascena var. trigintipetala</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
